53
00:02:22,240 --> 00:02:25,240
The first is to amend Figure 5-25.

54
00:02:25,240 --> 00:02:31,240
Basically, a portion of the map was left out during the last update to the land development code.

55
00:02:31,240 --> 00:02:33,240
We're requesting that that be put back in.

56
00:02:33,240 --> 00:02:42,240
Now, the bulk of this request are amendments to the special requirements plan and special requirements map.

57
00:02:42,340 --> 00:02:50,340
At present, these do not allow for any type of office to be on the first floor of units fronting Broadway and a couple of the side streets.

58
00:02:50,340 --> 00:02:54,340
A map is included within the ordinance language.

59
00:02:54,340 --> 00:03:06,340
Now, this proposed ordinance would remove that restriction and basically allow for not complete office on the first floor of Broadway, but finance, real estate, and insurance offices.

60
00:03:06,439 --> 00:03:12,439
Before, I wanted to give you a little bit of a background as to why that restriction was actually in place.

61
00:03:12,439 --> 00:03:18,439
So in 1998, going way, way back, there was a stakeholder committee that was put together by the City Commission.

62
00:03:18,439 --> 00:03:23,439
And they were tasked with reviewing the B-1 zoning district.

63
00:03:23,439 --> 00:03:26,439
That was the zoning district that was in place at that time.

64
00:03:26,439 --> 00:03:28,439
There's a map included in your backup.

65
00:03:28,439 --> 00:03:32,439
But basically, it was Broadway and then about a block off of Broadway.

66
00:03:32,539 --> 00:03:54,539
They were tasked with that because they wanted to review both the land development code requirements, stakeholder interests, as well as the CRA, the community redevelopment area, design manual, and master plan to make sure that everything was aligned and basically to make recommendations to the City Commission about any improvements that could be made to the B-1 zoning district.

67
00:03:54,639 --> 00:04:07,639
As a result of that, the presentation to the City Commission at the time was that because of the city's goals to provide a more human-scaled downtown, promote storefronts, and promote active retail and restaurant uses,

68
00:04:07,639 --> 00:04:14,639
they requested that all office be removed from the first floor fronting Broadway within the B-1 zoning district.

69
00:04:14,639 --> 00:04:19,639
Those changes were made in 1999 and have been in place since.

70
00:04:19,740 --> 00:04:28,740
I would like to mention that these were further, these are further enhanced by the form-based code that was adopted in 2020.

71
00:04:28,740 --> 00:04:33,740
At that time, we actually expanded not only to Broadway but to, again, a couple of the side streets.

72
00:04:33,740 --> 00:04:48,740
Again, this is also supported, this human-scaled development interest is supported by the single-laning of Broadway under the Kanaka semi-development and various other projects that we've had going on over the last almost 30 years.

73
00:04:48,839 --> 00:05:03,839
Now, in December of 2025, the City Commission did direct staff to remove this restriction for finance, insurance, real estate offices on the first floor fronting Broadway and directed staff to do so, considering it would open up these standards.

74
00:05:03,839 --> 00:05:07,839
So, considering that, staff is recommending approval.

75
00:05:08,839 --> 00:05:09,839
